 used to identify the root causes of a problem by categorizing potential causes.\"", "\"5 WHYS\":\"The 5 Whys is a problem-solving technique that involves asking 'why' five times to drill down to the root cause of a problem.\"", "\"PDCA CYCLE\":\"The PDCA Cycle (Plan-Do-Check-Act) is a four-step model for continuous improvement in business processes.\"", "\"GEMBA WALK\":\"A Gemba Walk is a practice where managers go to the 'Gemba' (the place where work is done) to observe processes and identify opportunities for improvement.\"", "\"KANBAN\":\"Kanban is a visual scheduling system used in Lean Manufacturing to manage work and inventory at every stage of production.\"", "\"5S\":\"5S is a workplace organization method that uses five Japanese words: Seiri (Sort), Seiton (Set in order), Seiso (Shine), Seiketsu (Standardize), and Shitsuke (Sustain).\"", "\"INTERPRETING TPAR\":\"TPAR is interpreted as follows: If TPAR > 1, the product is profitable as the throughput contribution exceeds the fixed costs. If TPAR = 1, the product breaks even. If TPAR < 1, the product is loss-making as the throughput contribution does not cover the fixed costs required to make it.\"", "\"WAYS TO IMPROVE TPAR\":\"Ways to improve TPAR include eliminating bottlenecks or reducing the time spent on bottleneck resources, reducing other factory costs, increasing selling prices, or reducing material costs. However, increasing selling prices may not be feasible in a competitive environment, and reducing material costs may affect quality.\"", "\"ENVIRONMENTAL ISSUES\":\"Environmental issues include global warming caused by greenhouse gas emissions, depletion of global reserves of scarce natural resources, and pollution and rising sea levels causing loss of habitats for many species.\"", "\"IMPORTANCE OF THE ENVIRONMENT FOR BUSINESS\":\"The importance of the environment for business includes the impact of poor environmental behavior on an organization's image, potential loss of sales due to customer boycotts, and heavy fines imposed by governments for harming the environment.\"", "\"ENVIRONMENTAL BEHAVIOUR AND PERFORMANCE\":\"Environmental behavior and performance can improve a company's performance by becoming more aware of its impact on the environment. Poor environmental behavior can harm an organization's image, leading to a loss of sales, and governments may impose heavy fines on companies that harm the environment.\"", "\"COST PER FACTORY HOUR\":\"Cost per factory hour is calculated as Other factory costs divided by Bottleneck resource hours available.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}